, 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{G}=\sum_{l=1}^{r_{\mathbf{G}}}s_{l}^{\mathbf{G}}\mathbf{G}_{1}^{l}\circ\dots\circ\mathbf{G}_{d}^{l},
\]

\end_inset

and an acceptable error 
\begin_inset Formula $\epsilon$
\end_inset

, we attempt to find a representation 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{F}=\sum_{\tilde{l}=1}^{r_{\mathbf{F}}}s_{\tilde{l}}^{\mathbf{F}}\mathbf{F}_{1}^{\tilde{l}}\circ\dots\circ\mathbf{F}_{d}^{\tilde{l}}
\]

\end_inset

with 
\begin_inset Formula $r_{\mathbf{F}}<r_{\mathbf{G}}$
\end_inset

, such that 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\Vert \mathbf{F}-\mathbf{G}\right\Vert /\left\Vert \mathbf{G}\right\Vert <\epsilon$
\end_inset

.
