\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
The TT-DMRG-cross approach solves,
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\textrm{min}_{G_{1}\dots G_{d}}\left\Vert \mathbf{U}-\mathbf{U}_{TT}\right\Vert ,
\]

\end_inset

by optimizing over two cores, 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{k}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{k+1}$
\end_inset

, at the same time.
 The important cores
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
W_{k}\left(i_{k},i_{k+1}\right)=G_{k}\left(i_{k}\right)G_{k+1}\left(i_{k+1}\right),
\]

\end_inset

are found using the maximum volume principle and 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{k}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $G_{k+1}$
\end_inset

 are recovered via the SVD.
 
\end_layout

